Class TableswitchChoicePoint

All Implemented Interfaces:
ChoicePoint
public class TableswitchChoicePoint
extends SwitchingChoicePoint

A TableswitchChoicePoint is generated whenever one the instruction tableswitch is reached and the element on top of the operand stack of the executed frame is not constant. The choice point will make sure that all possible jumping targets are evaluated.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

TableswitchChoicePoint

public TableswitchChoicePoint(Frame frame,
                              int pc,
                              int pcNext,
                              de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Term termFromStack,
                              de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant[] keys,
                              int[] pcs,
                              de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant low,
                              de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant high)
                       throws SymbolicExecutionException
Create the tableswitch choice point.

Parameters:
frame - The currently executed Frame.
pc - The pc of the instruction that generates the ChoicePoint.
pcNext - The pc of the instruction after the lcmp instruction.
termFromStack - The term term that was on top of the stack. Using the non symbolic execution, this would be the key for the switch.
keys - The possible keys.
pcs - The possible jump targets.
low - The "low" boundary of the tableswitch instruction.
high - The "high" boundary of the tableswitch instruction.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the number of keys is not equal to the number of jump targets or if there are no choices at all.
java.lang.NullPointerException - If either of the specified arrays or the boundaries is null.
SymbolicExecutionException - On fatal problems applying the constraint.
